<http://dx.doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.4407124>
        a                        fabio:Figure ;
        dc:description           "FIGURE 22. Oodes gracilis A. Villa & G.B. Villa, 1833 (A–B: neotype; C: male specimen, Bulgaria, Dragoman Marsh; D–E: male specimen, Bulgaria, Srebarna Lake; F–G: female specimens, Bulgaria, Dragoman Marsh). A, C: median lobe of aedeagus, left lateral view; B, D: same, dorsal view; E: same, ventral view; F: left gonocoxite, ventral view; G: spermathecal complex and gonocoxites, ventral view. Scale lines = 0.5 mm (Figs A–E, G); = 0.2 mm (Fig. F)." ;
        fabio:hasRepresentation  "https://zenodo.org/record/4407124/files/figure.png" .

<http://dx.doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.4407118>
        a                        fabio:Figure ;
        dc:description           "FIGURE 19. Oodes helopioides (Fabricius, 1792) (A–B: Oodes thessalonicensis Schatzmayr, 1909, lectotype; C–D: male specimen, Bulgaria, Veleka River outfall; E–F: male specimen, Bulgaria, Srebarna Lake; G: female specimen, same locality; H: female specimen, same locality). A, E: median lobe of aedeagus, left lateral view; B–C: same, anterior dorsal view; D: same, posterior dorsal view; F: same, ventral view; G: left gonocoxite, ventral view; H: spermathecal complex and gonocoxites, ventral view. Scale lines = 0.5 mm (Figs A–F, H); = 0.2 mm (Fig. G)." ;
        fabio:hasRepresentation  "https://zenodo.org/record/4407118/files/figure.png" .

